OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1780553101
OL,3,CFormer Travelodge manager says she was
OL,4,Csexually assaulted on a night shift
OL,6,F"They called the main reception and
OL,7,Fwhen I answered the phone, he said,
OL,8,F'There she is', and then gave me a
OL,9,Fbarrel of abuse."
OL,11,FIt was after this that Rebecca
OL,12,Freported the incident to the police.
OL,14,F"The first thing the police said to me
OL,15,Fwas, why did you not report this when
OL,16,Fit happened? And I said, 'my company
OL,17,Ftold me not to'."
OL,19,FWe took this claim to Travelodge
OL,20,Fseveral times, but they weren't able
OL,21,Fto comment on it.
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@QO]vD@AOUyD@QO]
