OL,3,CFormer Travelodge manager says she was
OL,4,Csexually assaulted on a night shift
OL,6,FStaff at many branches are required to
OL,7,Fwork solo shifts armed with a personal
OL,8,Fsafety alarm that connects them to an
OL,9,Fexternal company that can monitor
OL,10,Faudio when activated.
OL,12,FRebecca is sceptical of the safety of
OL,13,Fmembers of staff and customers in
OL,14,Ftheir hotels.
OL,16,F"Our staff work long night shifts,
OL,17,Feight-hour shifts or more, and they
OL,18,Fare completely on their own dealing
OL,19,Fwith drunks, drug abusers, and violent
OL,20,Fguests. You name it, they deal with
OL,21,Fit."
OL,26,@xD@AOU
